= Developing with the Eclipse IDE =

	1.  Install the PyDev extension in eclipse (http://pydev.org/updates)
	2.  Install MercurialEclipse (http://cbes.javaforge.com/update)
	3.  Install Eclipse Web Developer tools from indigo (already in updates)
	4.  Create a new Mercurial project that clones the repo
	5.  Close Eclipse
	6.  copy .pydevproject.bak to .pydevproject
	7.  Run /my/local/python bootstrap.py from the new project directory
	8.  Run bin/buildout - this will install all the required dependencies and reconfigure pydev
	9.  Restart Eclipse
	10.  Right-click on the project: PyDev > Set as Pydev Project
	11. Right-click on the project: PyDev > Set as Django Project
	12. Run the tool using run as "Pydev: Django"
	
Reference:

	http://pydev.org/manual_101_project_conf2.html